--to check if rabbitq is present and it's status
    sc query RABBITMQ
--to stop rabbitmq
    sc stop RABBITMQ

--to start rabbitmq
        sc start RABBITMQ

Kafka vs RABBITMQ
    --kafka is distributed event streaming platform, while rabbitmq is message broker
    --data retention: kafka stores data on disk, rabbitmq stores data in memory
    --performance: kafka is generally faster
    --scalability: kafka is highly scalable
